Caron was born as the child of immigrants from the
neighboring country of Tarasa. Her mother used her beauty to
engage with nobles and members of the Senate as a
prostitute. It could be said that the only job available for
immigrants from enemy countries was that of a prostitute.

Caron's mother entrusted her daughter with what could be
called her own curse of desires. As a result, she devoted
her entire life to Caron's education. It was within this
twisted affection that Caron's personality was formed.

Caron's life without her mother. Days of being pointed at as
the daughter of a prostitute. For Caron, everyone except her
mother is a stranger, and since the day she lost her mother,
she has been the only one she can trust.

The letter entrusted to Caron by her mother would change her
life. Eventually, it would even change the future of the
empire.
